    "description": "Discipline: Neigong\nSkill: Meditation against Parry\nType: Normal\nQi: 3\n\nYou adopt a meditative posture and bring to life an invisible sword that strikes against your enemies. When performed precisely this Technique can be devastating. Roll Meditation against Parry. On a Success you strike your opponent with an invisible blade that does 2d10 plus 1d10 Damage per Rank of Neigong. On a Total Success you call forth three additional blades, inflicting 3 Extra Wounds. Because the blades are invisible they impose a -1 to Parry per Rank of Neigong. Cathartic: Same as above except on a Total Success you call forth 8 more blades, inflicting 8 Extra Wounds.",
